@NODE imp " IMPORTANT NOTES"
Version 2.6  - You can now store your data files (language file, config, etc.)
               in any directory you wish. Upon startup, M-Scan will look for
               'DLGConfig:Master/M-Scan'. If this file doesn't exist, then
               M-Scan will assume 'Master:' to be the directory where you
               have your data files stored.

Version 2.7  - Read the section on verbose output!
             - Please don't put this into general distribution!

Version 2.7a - Only the one major change with verbose output.
             - Includes some requestors during start-up to help those who
               have reported problems during start-up.

Version 2.8  - No changes required by sysop.

@ENDNODE
@NODE What_is_itd " What is M-Scan?"

M-Scan is a file scanner for DLG BB/OS. It has the following features:

  o Shows new files in users global newscan listed areas.
  o Sysop settable option to sort global list before scanning.
  o Allows range tagging for easy input.
  o Offers full global scanning with wildcard support.
  o Very FAST! Will scan approx. 27500 files/min. on my A3000/Q540S
  o Correctly adds tagged files in sorted order to batch list.
  o Checks global file paths if file not found in proper directory.
  o Is fully functional, even when not registered.
  o Shows search matches in highlight and upper case.
  o Shows age of files listed.
  o Can display more of the description.

M-Scan forms part of the M-Tag package. For information on the M-Tag package,
see the AmigaGUIDE file included in the M-Tag package.

@ENDNODE

@NODE language " Language support?"

Customiseable language support has now been added!

The string file is called @{"DLGConfig:Master/M-Scan.{language}" link imp} and follows the
same rules as the @{"language file for M-TagFS" link M-TagFS.Guide/custr}.

Notes about this language file:

       - There are no strings which require the ,S operater.
       - Line 1 of the language file is the sequence to turn OFF the cursor.
         You may leave this blank if you don't want the cursor turned off.
       - Line 42 of the language file turns the cursor back on!

@ENDNODE
@NODE config " M-Scan's config file"

M-Scan can now have some of its colors configured by the sysop. To do this, a
config file is required.

The config file is called '@{"DLGConfig:Master/M-Tag.cfg" link imp}'.

If you look at the config, you will see it also contains the configs for
other programs in the M-Tag package.

Valid keywords for M-Scan are:

SCANTAGDISPLAY=

       This is the display color config line. See the included config file
       on how to change these colors.

       Example:   SCANTAGDISPLAY=625166152

       NOTE:      This keyword is also used for M-Tag


MASSTAG=

       This keyword enables/disables the tagging of all files listed with 1
       keypress.

       Example:   MASSTAG=ON
                  MASSTAG=OFF

       Default:   OFF

       NOTE:      This keyword is also used for M-Tag


MAXTAG=

       This keyword allows you to set the maximum number of tagged files the
       user can tag from within M-Scan.

       NOTE:      This keyword is also used for M-TagFS and M-Tag.


RATIOBLOCK=

       This keyword en/disables ratio checking. When on, the user will not
       be able to tag a file if the file will exceed their ratio.

       Example:   RATIOBLOCK=ON
       Example:   RATIOBLOCK=OFF
       Default:   RATIOBLOCK=ON

       NOTE:      This keyword is also used for M-TagFS and M-Tag.


TIMEWARN=

       This keyword turns on/off time warning. This feature will warn the
       user that they no longer have the time to download the files they
       have tagged. It only displays a message when they tag a file.

       Example: TIMEWARN=ON
       Example: TIMEWARN=OFF
       Default: TIMEWARN=ON

       NOTE:      This keyword is also used for M-TagFS and M-Tag.


@ENDNODE
@NODE Setting_upd " How to Install M-Scan"

Call M-Scan thus:

  M-Scan <Parameter list>

       Order and case of parameter's are NOT important!

  Where <Parameter list> is one or more of the following parameters:

       -A     Do NOT ask if the user wishes to check for new files. Used in
              conjunction with -L only.

       -B     This turns on a special mode. It shows all new files in all
              accessable areas in the users current SIG. REQUIRES the -S
              parameter!

       -D     This parameter is used with the -G parameter. It will by-pass
              the search menu and goes into 'days old' mode.

       @{b}-F     Force the user into their current SIG. If not on, the user
              will be asked if they wish to work in current SIG or all areas.@{bu}

       -FF    Force the user to use M-Scan's fast mode (original mode), and
              don't give them the option of using a verbose display.

       -G     Perform a global search as opposed to a login search.

       -K     This parameter is used in conjunction with the -G parameter.
              It will by-pass the search menu and go into keyword mode.

       -L     Run in login mode. Shows all new files in users global newscan
              file list.

       -N     Set default responce to NO when asked if you want to check for
              new files.

       -O     Sort the users global newscan list before scanning. Used with
              -L option only.

       -P     Do NOT update the pointers when run in one of the new file
              search modes.

       -Q     Run in quick mode. Mainly for sysops with fast machines/small
              areas and fast modems. It suppresses the printing of area name
              during scanning, printing the area number only.

       -R     This parameter is used to display the files real numbers.
              Unfortunately, due to the way M-Scan sets up the taggable list
              of files, this option must also disable tagging of files.

       -S     Pass the current file SIG. Will ask the user if they wish to
              search within the SIG or all areas (unless -F is used).

       -T     This parameter is used in conjunction with either -B or -L.
              It will automatically skip any area the user has not yet been
              to. Otherwise, it adds the user and displays new files in
              that area.

       -U     Used in conjunction with -B or -L, this parameter will cause
              M-Scan to exit if the user has made less than 2 calls.

       -V<n>  The number of lines of description to display. Eg: -V6 to
              display the first 6 lines. Default is 6, maximum is set at
              run-time according to the users screen length. Note that M-Scan
              will check to see if the maximum description will fit on-screen
              and if it won't, it'll bring up the tag prompt.

By default, -G is assumed.

If you specify -G, the user will get a menu allowing them to do a keyword
search, days old search, global newscan new file search, or all areas new
file search.

You will also need @{"M-Support" Link M-Support.guide/Main}.  This program creates the users valid area
list upon login.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Verbose " Verbose output"

This mode will allow the user to search more of the description (up to 8K),
and also to display more of the description.  Without the -FF switch, the
user is asked if they wish to use this mode.  There are 3 lines in the
language file dedicated to this function.  Lines 44 and 45 are the prompt
sent to the user to ask them if they wish to use this mode.  Line 46 is an
alternate title line.

Because of the drop in speed, there is a twirly to show the user that
something is indeed happening.

The reason there is the -FF switch, and no corresponding switch to force the
user to use verbose mode, is because verbose mode would annoy some people
no-end.

NOTE: Because this mode uses the .fd files in conjunction with the quick
      index, it is MUCH slower, and a bigger drain on system resources.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Historyd " History of M-Scan"

Version 0.5á - Initial release. Only sent to one other site for initial
               impressions.

Version 0.6á - Added area over-write instead of scrolling down page.
             - Added a '[PRESS RETURN]' at end of output.

Version 0.7á - Added M-Tag CD support.
             - Added full global file searching.
             - Removed registered info on exit under certain conditions.
             - Added abort routine.
             - Changed output a little.

Version 0.8á - Fixed a bug in the login tagging routine.

Version 1.0  - Added global filepaths support.

Version 1.0a - Fixed a bug which caused enforcer hits, and perhaps crashed
               some machines.
             - Added option to enter another search option without having to
               re-run M-Scan.
             - Added -F option.

Version 1.0b - Fixed a small display error.
             - Added option to tag a non-existant file anyway.

Version 1.0c - Fixed a severe bug when more than 255 files tagged.
             - Fixed even more severe bug when more than 127 files tagged.
               This bug appears to be in DLG itself.

Version 1.1  - Fixed a bug in the -F option. This was causing the program to
               run much slower, rather than faster. Now shows a significant
               speed increase.
             - Beefed error trapping up in a few places.
             - Fixed a nasty bug which was causing some machines to crash
               when exiting M-Scan.

Version 1.2  - Changed the way newscan's are handled. Now is considerably
               faster.
             - Added -O option.
             - Now uses area list as output by M-Support for newscan.
             - Now reprints current area if more than a screenfull of files
               are shown.
             - Added 1 line stats at end of each pass.
             - Does not update high pointer of current area if user reaches
               tag list limit.
             - Now handles users separating numbers by comma's!

Version 1.2a - Fixed a harmless logic error which slowed operation down. Now
               is about 30% faster when searching!
             - Removed 1 line stats when doing a new file scan.

Version 2.0  - Fixed a bug where the 1 line stats weren't being zero'd after
               a search.
             - Optimised some operations. Now marginally faster when
               initiating
             - Removed title changing!

Version 2.0a - Fixed a problem when searching within a SIG. Could cause the
               system to hang!

Version 2.09 - Fixed a bug which would show a file area number 0 when working
               within a SIG.
             - Optimized SIG locating a bit.
             - Added option to ask if user wishes to scan new files for all
               cases of new file scanning.
             - Added option for default of NO when asking for new file scan.
             - Released to 1 sysop only.

Version 2.1  - Fixed several bugs introduced into 2.09
             - Added a short message to inform user that a SIG is being
               loaded. Under heavy use, this could take a while.
             - Added option to tag all listed files.
             - Added configurable color to some parts.

Version 2.1a - Added config keyword: MAXTAG. See M-TagFS.Guide for details.

Version 2.2  - Optimised scanning. Now quicker on wildcards, and
               considerably quicker on non-wildcards.
             - Removed -F option. Now runs in the old FAST mode always.
             - Added new option -F to force user into current SIG.
             - Added 'days old' option.
             - Added Global Newscan search for new files.
             - Added full area search for new files.
             - Added -Q option.
             - Removed 'H' option from new files menu. Users should know what
               they are being asked :-)
             - Added RATIOBLOCK keyword.
             - Added -K parameter.
             - Added -D parameter.
             - Added -P parameter.
             - Added -T parameter.
             - Added -U parameter.
             - Added -R parameter.
             - Added TIMEWARN keyword.

Version 2.2a - Made FREE files pass the ratio test.
             - Fixed a fatal bug in the -T parameter.

Version 2.3  - A few minor changes.

Version 2.4  - A few more very minor changes!

Version 2.4a - Fixed a small buglet in cursor on/off operations.

Version 2.5  - Finally made most strings in the program configurable.

Version 2.6  - When searching for a file, and not using a wildcard, M-Scan
               now makes the matched pattern uppercase and yellow on blue
               or reversed if in mono mode (Yeah!).
             - Now displays files larger than 999K as a Megabyte value.
             - Now displays the age of the file in hours, days, or years,
               depending on file age.
             - Descriptions now conform to the user's screen width.
             - Now uses 'pointers.file' to get high file number. Previously,
               if a file area had not been renumbered after files were
               removed, then new files would be missed.
             - Can now use a different path for data files.
             - Added title line to top of display.
             - Now replaces all CR's and LF's from the description with
               spaces, rather than cutting the description off at these
               characters.
             - Not released!

Version 2.7  - Added verbose output mode. See the verbose output section
               for details.
             - Only released on my InterNet mailing list.

Version 2.7a - Changed the way verbose mode works. Now is MUCH faster when
               description's are less then 60 characters long.

Version 2.8  - Made a few small optimisations.
             - Fixed a bug which would cause a screen length  over-run when
               in verbose mode.
             - Fixed a bug which would chew 4196 bytes if you quite during
               the verbose mode and in the middle of an area.
             - Increased description buffer from 4096 Bytes to 8192 Bytes.
             - Fixed a bug when tagging in verbose mode.
             - Fixed a bug which caused garbage to be displayed on the
               screen.
             - Tidied up verbose display of descriptions a little.

Version 2.8b - Fixed a small display error which would print the wrong info
               line at the top of each screen.

Version 2.8c - Changed the display of the area name and twirly in verbose
               mode. Should now display things a little neater when going
               to a new screen.

Version 2.8d - Put a small delay in if M-Scan could not create an area list.

Version 2.9  - Fixed a bug in calculating the user's ratio.

@ENDNODE

@NODE john " Special thanks"

Special thanks to John Veldthuis of Virus Checker fame.

He has taken some time to poke around inside GFA executables and has located
the problem causing a 40 byte memory loss to occur in EVERY GFA program you
run.

There are lots of sysops out there who's system memory will be eternally
gratefull. See @{"GFA's problem" link M-TagP.guide/GFA} for an overview of the problem.

@ENDNODE
